						<summary>

						<p>This records the gift of a silver vessal weighing 30 <hi rend="italic">Īḻakkāśu</hi> for offering water to the god during worship, by <hi rend="bold">Aiyaṉ Māraśiṅgaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Vīraśēkhara-Mūvēndavēḷāṉ</hi> the donor mentioned in No. 312 above. <hi rend="bold">Vīraśēkhara</hi> was possibly a title of king <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
